## M20a.2 negative: `self` parameter at position other than first.
##
## Per GPT-5.5's M20a.2 design pass: "self must be first param if
## present as receiver." Before M20a.2, second-position `self` was
## silently accepted, and the call site would either bind the wrong
## argument or fall through to a confusing arity error.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: `self` must be the first parameter.

struct User
  name: String

  fun bad(other: Int, ?self) -> Int
    other

sub main()
  u = User(name: "x")
  print(u.bad(42))
